description:
Briefly, according to one aspect of the present invention, a camera apparatus comprises:



        a) a zoom lens having a zoom focus setting that is adjustable over a range of focus values;
        b) control circuitry for generating a variable voltage potential according to the zoom focus setting;
        c) a flash illumination apparatus comprising a light source and a variable focus lens, the variable focus lens comprising:

            i) a first and a second fluid in a chamber, the fluids having different indices of refraction, the fluids being non-miscible and being in contact over an interface surface with variable shape; and
            ii) an electrode for applying the variable voltage potential within the chamber for shaping the interface surface according to the zoom focus setting.
